# FA2 — Investigation
Evaluation of [Sample A](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PUHLmO_z-7yDTwkbqUu4LgvGp3dfukKN/view)
![strengths limitations appraisal.png](data:image/png;base64,)

### Strengths & Limitations: 

| Strengths                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         | Limitations                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |
| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| An action plan includes the task to be done on each day and a description of the task, stating clearly what is to be done.                                                                                                                                                                                                        | The action plan should include how a task will be achieved and not just about the task itself.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| The research question includes the issue (effect of sustainable resource extraction on Japanese construction workers), time (1980s) and place (Japan). This provides a detailed and focused research question to guide the student’s research, while at the same time not restricting the research to one or two topics of focus. | It gives a start date “from 1980…” but not an end date, which somewhat reduces the focus of the question. This can be avoided by giving fixed years as the start and end dates, i.e. 19xx to 20xx.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| The guiding question was broken down efficiently with the use of a mind map. This simplification of the question contributes to the investigation as it has led to detailed sub-questions being created which makes it comprehensive.                                                                                             | The research done for the first guiding question does not go in depth enough about the new technology of the time, only vaguely stating the basic facts of their time of creation and original purpose. Mentioning their uses, how they work, etc. would help lengthening this response to address the question better.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | “The wages decreased and the wages of the older world have decreased because they are aged and robots are replacing them.” — not justified or explained, only vaguely explains the graph. This response does not fully answer the question it is answering, and requires further explanation and elaboration as to how this information was collected and how it connects to the question.                                                                                                                                                                                            |
|                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | Research for “Did anyone get hired or fired in those companies after the transition?” is not relevant to the research question, nor is its importance and requirement for answering the research question explained. It is also not backed up by statistics or any form of evidence, and simply makes statements such as “The retired and aged workers can get replaced by robots to perform tasks such as welding, shipping and basic tasks involving the construction of a high rise building.” The “robots” mentioned here are not explained further, simply stated in the answer. |
|                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | The guiding questions don’t mention research about past practices, removing the opportunity for comparing current and past practices.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| All the sources are mentioned and are in the correct format (MLA), stating the necessary information such as the title of the article, the publisher, and the date published.                                                                                                                                                     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
